随着移动互联网的快速发展，iOS 平台的 Live Photo 与 Android 平台的 Motion Photo 已成为用户日常拍摄的重要媒体形式。然而，两种动态图片的底层格式存在根本性差异：Live Photo 由独立的 JPEG 图像文件与 MOV 视频文件通过 XMP 元数据中的 UUID 关联构成；Motion Photo 则将 MP4 视频以二进制方式追加至 JPEG 文件末尾，并在 JPEG 头部 APP1 段的 XMP 中记录视频偏移量。这种格式异构性导致动态图片在跨平台传输和展示时面临严重的兼容问题。
本文设计并实现了一套跨平台动态图片兼容系统。系统采用 Spring Boot 构建后端服务，分别针对 iOS Live Photo 和 Android Motion Photo 实现了两套格式解析器：前者通过扫描 JPEG APP1 标记段提取 XMP 中的 apple-fi:AssetIdentifier 来配对 JPEG 与 MOV 文件；后者从 JPEG 头部 APP1 段定位 XMP，读取 GContainer:Item 中的视频偏移量以分离封面图与视频流。解析完成后，系统调用 FFmpeg 将视频统一转码为 H.264/AAC 编码的 MP4 格式，并将封面图与视频文件分别存储至 MinIO 对象存储，以统一的 DYNAMIC_PHOTO 消息类型通过 WebSocket 实现实时传输。客户端基于 Flutter 框架实现，采用单一播放逻辑屏蔽平台来源差异，支持长按封面预览视频、单击全屏播放的交互体验。
实验结果表明，系统能够正确解析来自 iOS 和 Android 两大平台的动态图片，格式识别准确率达 100%，在标准测试环境下 Live Photo 端到端处理延迟约 1.2 秒，Motion Photo 约 0.9 秒，满足即时通信场景的使用需求。
关键词：动态图片；Live Photo；Motion Photo；跨平台兼容；FFmpeg 转码；Flutter

Abstract
With the rapid development of mobile Internet, iOS Live Photo and Android Motion Photo have become important media formats in users' daily photography. However, the underlying formats of these two dynamic photo types differ fundamentally: Live Photo consists of a standalone JPEG image and a MOV video file associated through a UUID stored in XMP metadata; Motion Photo appends an MP4 video in binary to the end of a JPEG file, with the video offset recorded in the XMP within the JPEG APP1 segment header. This format heterogeneity causes severe compatibility issues when dynamic photos are transmitted and displayed across platforms.
This paper designs and implements a cross-platform dynamic photo compatibility system. The backend service is built with Spring Boot and implements two dedicated format parsers: the Live Photo parser locates the apple-fi:AssetIdentifier from the XMP in the JPEG APP1 marker to pair JPEG and MOV files; the Motion Photo parser reads the XMP from the JPEG header APP1 segment to obtain the GContainer:Item video offset and separate the cover image from the video stream. After parsing, FFmpeg transcodes the video to H.264/AAC MP4 format, and both the cover image and video are stored in MinIO object storage. A unified DYNAMIC_PHOTO message type is delivered in real time via WebSocket. The Flutter-based client implements a single playback logic that abstracts platform-specific differences, supporting long-press preview and tap-to-fullscreen interactions.
Experimental results show that the system correctly parses dynamic photos from both iOS and Android platforms with 100% format recognition accuracy. Under standard test conditions, the end-to-end processing latency is approximately 1.2 seconds for Live Photo and 0.9 seconds for Motion Photo, meeting the requirements of instant messaging scenarios.
Keywords: Dynamic Photo; Live Photo; Motion Photo; Cross-platform Compatibility; FFmpeg Transcoding; Flutter

 
